                <head>No. 635<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>For extensive documentation on the Geneva Conference, April 26–July 21, 1954,
                    which was largely concerned with matters relating to Korea and Indochina, see
                        <ref target="frus1952-54v16">volume XVI</ref>. The documentation presented
                    in that volume includes exchanges of correspondence between President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> and President <persName
                        corresp="#p_COTYR1">Coty</persName>, and between Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> and Foreign Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_BIDAULTG1">Bidault</persName>, as well as records of numerous
                    United States-French meetings concerning the outcome of the negotiations which
                    took place during both the formal and informal meetings at the Geneva
                    Conference.</p>
            </div>
